{
  "stem": "9538.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the meantime, more transports came from Germany, from Czechoslovakia, and from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents were still with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The last-- and I, as a nurse, went to Skirotava with sledges.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not myself, a few of us went to Skirotava with sledges to-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I can't say greet-- to, to help to bring them into the ghetto, you know, on the sledges, to put little children on the sledges.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we told them not to go into these-- into these lorries.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They should try to, to walk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that's why we came with sledges.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had old people on the sledges, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that's why I know the last transport arrived in February of '42.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The SS had a big warehouse in Riga, where the clothes of the Jews were collected.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Jewish people had to work there and sort out the best thing to be sent back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SIGH] That's why we know that so many had arrived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They went, some, to-- I don't know what, what happened to the clothes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, they went to this sorting station, which was outside the ghetto where German Jews and Latvian Jews worked--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to sort them out and pack them to be sent back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whether they sent them to, to bombed-out people, or whether they sent them to the Russian Front for the soldiers, that, that I don't know-- what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But no, no Jews came to the ghetto after February of '42.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In February-- in the meantime, there were shootings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if people were caught with something, or if you talked to the Jews-- to the Latvian Jews on the opposite side, they would shoot you.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, there were dead people every day lying there.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
